The paper discusses learning properties of stochastic gradient methods, which are commonly used in machine learning and optimization. The focus is on analyzing the effects of multiple passes over the data and mini-batches on regularization properties and convergence rates. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
